      • IRElection

        public IRElection​(java.lang.String fileName,
                  java.lang.String outputPath,
                  int candidateCount,
                  Candidate[] candidates,
                  Party[] parties,
                  Ballot[] ballots)
        This is the constructor for the IRElection class. It inherits from the Election class. It will be initialized with the following parameters to instantiate an IRElection.
        Parameters:
        fileName - a string representing the file to be opened by the system
        outputPath - a string designating the output destination on the user's sysyem
        candidateCount - an integer representing the number of candidates in the election
        candidates - an array of Candidate objects consisting of all candidates in the election
        parties - an array of Party objects containing one instance of each party that is present in an election
        ballots - an array of Ballot objects containing all ballots cast in an election

    • Method Detail

      • redistribute

        public void redistribute()
        This method is used when votes need to be redistributed after a candidate has been eliminated.

      • process_media

        public void process_media()
        This method processes the data from the election and writes the occurrences of the election to the output file. The outcomes from each round are displayed and each step in the process of elimination is tracked until there is a winner of the election. The output is written either to the given file name or is named at the time of processing. Catches I/O exceptions if the given file name is invalid.
        Overrides:
        process_media in class Election
